The Minister of Natural Resources and Tourism, Dr Damas Ndumbaro has asked people living in protected areas surroundings to stop conducting their activities in such places because they are catchment areas of 95 per cent of the water used in the country. Speaking on Thursday (March 4, 2021) while opening the Worldâ€™s Wildlife Day Conference, celebrated nationally in Morogoro region, he said every citizen is responsible for protecting the reserved areas for the betterment of the country. Elaborating, he noted the misuse of such areas can lead to the damage of water sources and turn into water scarcity in the country. "95 per cent of the water used in the country comes from protected areas so they should be maintained and not damaged to unsure no water shortages," said Dr Ndumbaro.